# Hybrid Performance App - Cursor Rules

## Tech Stack & Core Architecture
- Backend: Python 3.11+ / FastAPI (Asynchronous programming with async/await)
- Database: PostgreSQL via Supabase (Always design schemas for relational integrity)
- AI: Google Gemini 2.5 Flash Lite via Google AI Studio API
- Native integrations: iOS HealthKit, Android Health Connect (API layer only)

## Coding Standards & Guidelines (Python/FastAPI)
- Use Pydantic v2 for all Request/Response data validation models.
- Implement explicit type hinting everywhere.
- Write modular, clean, and reusable code. Separate routes, services, models, and schemas.
- Do not use global state; utilize FastAPI Dependency Injection (`Depends`) for DB sessions and authentication.
- All database operations must handle transaction rollbacks gracefully on error.

## Project Specific Rules
- Do NOT use LLM/AI for daily workout logging or volume/CNS calculations. These MUST be processed deterministically using python math logic and database queries to save token costs.
- AI should ONLY be invoked for weekly/monthly analysis, RAG operations, or programmatic adaptations.
- Always include `user_tier` ('free', 'premium', 'pro') checks in middleware or dependencies for rate-limiting AI features.
- Design database queries efficiently assuming an Always-Online network strategy.